tract for the development. The works include constructing 107 nos. of large diameter bored piles and ELS and construction of pile caps and ground beams.</p>',12.00),(79,'i4ljh5vfixc3aga4c4gxs378','Admiralty Integrated Station and SCL Enabling Works (South Island Line (East) – Contract 901)','2025-05-30 07:22:18.694000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.022000',NULL,8,36,'en','Admiralty Integrated Station and SCL Enabling Works','MTR Corporation Limited','18 May 2011 - 31 December 2016','<p>The South Island Line (East) is a medium-capacity railway connecting the MTR network at Admiralty to the Southern District of Hong Kong, via new stations at Ocean Park, Wong Chuk Hang, Lei Tung and South Horizons - a distance of approximately 7 km.</p><p>The primary objective of Contract 901 is to construct a new Admiralty Integrated Station in an urban centre with a very limited site area.  Under this contract, the existing Admiralty Station will be significantly extended to provide interchange facilities between the existing Tsuen Wan Line, the new South Island Line (East) and the proposed Shatin to Central Link. In addition to the four new platforms to be constructed below and adjacent to the existing station, the works include an interchange concourse, relocation of existing passenger entrances and external landscaping.</p><p>The Works under MTR Contract 901 comprise an extension east of the existing ADM station. The ADM integrated station will accommodate an interchange concourse, circulation areas and station cavern for SIL and SCL (Shatin Central Link). The extension is located under Harcourt Garden and is bounded by the existing ADM station, two existing finger platform box structures (Island Line and Tsuen Wan Line) and the existing underground Admiralty car park. The proposed platforms for SIL(E) and SCL will be constructed below and adjacent to the existing ADM.</p>',13.00),(81,'cdjz8giinphbed0tr0lqrem0','金钟综合车站及沙中綫前期工程 (南港岛綫(东段) - 合约编号901)','2025-05-30 07:25:01.188000','2025-07-07 07:15:21.370000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','金钟综合车站及沙中綫前期工程','香港铁路有限公司','2011 年 05 月 18 日 - 2016 年 12 月 31 日','<p>南港岛线主要连接香港岛中西区及南区,从金钟站出发,途经海洋公园、黄竹坑、利东及海怡半岛共五站,全长约7公里,车程需约10分钟,以中型铁路形式设计。</p><p>工程主要目标是在城市中心建造一个新的金钟综合车站,建造隧道连接到现有的金钟站。 工程完成后,现有的金钟站将会大大延伸,以提供现有荃湾线,南港岛线与沙田至中环线之间的换乘设施。 工程除了在现有车站毗邻下面建造四个新平台外,还包括交汇处,现有乘客出入口的搬迁和外部景观工程等。</p><p>地铁合约901工程包括延长现有金钟车站以东。 金钟车站可以将各线交汇,并提供中转区域及连接南港岛线和沙中线(沙田至中环线)。 延长部分的工程位于夏悫花园之下,并在现有的金钟车站、两个箱形结构的月台(港岛线及荃湾线)和现有的地下金钟停车场的范围内进行。 南港岛线(东段)和沙田至中环线月台则建造在现有金钟站之下的毗邻位置。</p>',13.00),(83,'m0jeqmkoaj6n2zs3qt9nndu4','金鐘綜合車站及沙中綫前期工程 (南港島綫(東段) - 合約編號901)','2025-05-30 07:25:42.059000','2025-07-07 07:15:23.423000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','金鐘綜合車站及沙中綫前期工程','香港鐵路有限公司','2011 年 05 月 18 日 - 2016 年 12 月 31 日','<p>南港島線主要連接香港島中西區及南區,從金鐘站出發,途經海洋公園、黃竹坑、利東及海怡半島共五站,全長約7公里,車程需約10分鐘,以中型鐵路形式設計。</p><p>工程主要目標是在城市中心建造一個新的金鐘綜合車站,建造隧道連接到現有的金鐘站。工程完成後,現有的金鐘站將會大大延伸,以提供現有荃灣線,南港島線與沙田至中環線之間的換乘設施。工程除了在現有車站毗鄰下面建造四個新平台外,還包括交匯處,現有乘客出入口的搬遷和外部景觀工程等。</p><p>地鐵合約901工程包括延長現有金鐘車站以東。金鐘車站可以將各線交匯,並提供中轉區域及連接南港島線和沙中線(沙田至中環線)。延長部分的工程位於夏愨花園之下,並在現有的金鐘車站、兩個箱形結構的月台(港島線及荃灣線)和現有的地下金鐘停車場的範圍內進行。南港島線(東段)和沙田至中環線月台則建造在現有金鐘站之下的毗鄰位置。</p>',13.00),(85,'dzsblg3vavlkpu49qp2q7az2','香港商用航空中心二號停機庫擴建工程(稱為三號停機庫)','2025-05-30 07:26:13.887000','2025-07-07 07:15:24.906000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','香港商用航空中心二號停機庫擴建工程(稱為三號停機庫)','香港商用航空中心','2011 年 05 月 14 日 - 2012 年 05 月 31 日','<p>此工程是香港商用航空中心二號停機庫的擴建工程，座落於二號停機庫旁,稱為三號停機庫。新的三號停機庫與現有的停機庫相得益彰，提供足夠的機庫空間以滿足香港飛機庫不斷增長的需求。</p><p>此工程主要包括建造一個有機庫門的鋼結構停機庫（約80米×50米），安裝停機庫內的鋼結構，並提供所有在工場必要的防護油漆塗料，建造一組一層高的輔助工場，停機坪工程，外部鋪設道路，工地工程，水管，渠務設施以及機械，通風和空調及電力裝置。</p>',14.00),(87,'dfrgy0jbqkaauzzi00f0u4jn','香港商用航空中心二号停机库扩建工程(称为三号停机库)','2025-05-30 07:26:45.246000','2025-07-07 07:15:20.893000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','香港商用航空中心二号停机库扩建工程(称为三号停机库)','香港商用航空中心','2011 年 05 月 14 日 - 2012 年 05 月 31 日','<p>此工程是香港商用航空中心二号停机库的扩建工程，座落于二号停机库旁,称为三号停机库。新的三号停机库与现有的停机库相得益彰，提供足够的机库空间以满足香港飞机库不断增长的需求。</p><p>此工程主要包括建造一个有机库门的钢结构停机库（约80米×50米），安装停机库内的钢结构，并提供所有在工场必要的防护油漆涂料，建造一组一层高的辅助工场，停机坪工程，外部铺设道路，工地工程，水管，渠务设施以及机械，通风和空调及电力装置。</p>',14.00),(89,'tchh4m3umbxvj4q6eoxvjri7','Proposed Extension to Hangar Two (also known as “Hangar Three”)','2025-05-30 07:29:45.083000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.483000',NULL,8,36,'en','Proposed Extension to Hangar Two (also known as “Hangar Three”)','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd.','14 May 2011 - 31 May 2012','<p>The project is the extension of the existing Hangar Two operated by Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd, namely as Hangar Three. The new third hangar aimed to complement the existing hangars in providing sufficient hangar spaces to meet the growing demand for aircraft hangars in Hong Kong.</p><p>Major works under the contract include the construction of an air-craft hangar building (approx. 80 m x 50m) with steel structure and metal cladding complete with hangar door, installation of the steel structure of the hangar building and providing all necessary protective painting at the fabrication yard and the construction of a group of one storey ancillary workshops, apron works, external paved roads, site works, plumbing, drainage installations and mechanical, ventilation and air conditioning and electrical installations.</p>',14.00),(91,'d9rixf64uvkn7kwhwtoah5k9','Tseung Kwan O Further Development – Design and Build of Infrastructure Works for Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill Site (Phase I) (Contract No. HY/2009/05)','2025-05-30 07:31:21.213000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.524000',NULL,8,36,'en','Tseung Kwan O Further Development – Design and Build of Infrastructure Works for Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill Site (Phase I)','Highways Department','29 December 2009 - 03 April 2012','<p>The Tseung Kwan O Further Development is to improve the overall design of the town with the vision to build Tseung Kwan O into a new town that can boast of its convenience, unique urban design of quality living environment.</p><p>This is one of the Tseung Kwan O Further Development projects, which mainly improves the linkage between Tseung Kwan O Stage 1 landfill site and the adjacent areas for s