9.524000',NULL,8,36,'en','Improvement Works at Lo Wu Station Platforms 1-3, Link Bridge and Concourse Extension','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','18 November 2002 - 30 July 2004','<p>The project included the installation of 156 nos. of vertical and raking mini piles with 273mm diameter to support the Concourse Extension of the Lo Wu Station and the Link Bridge linking the Concourse Extension to the existing Platform 1. The length of the piles constructed ranging from 20m to 40m with 5m long socket into Grade III rock. The piling works also included the Pre-Drilling prior to the commencement of the piling works to determine the rock head level and the target founding level. It also included the Proof Drilling subsequent to the completion of the pile installations.</p><br/><p>As all the works have to be carried out immediately next to the live railway tracks and inside the busy Lo Wu Station in full operation, the Contractor has to undertake all the necessary safety measures and arrangement to ensure that the train service and the operation of the Lo Wu Station will not be affected by the construction works.</p>',31.00),(200,'nac5qfqlnz6b0vxoj6zz852w','罗湖站改善工程：一号至三号站台，连接桥及车站大堂 (九广铁路 东铁合约编号：2002-0092)','2025-05-30 08:59:34.809000','2025-07-07 07:15:21.347000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','罗湖站改善工程：一号至三号站台，连接桥及车站大堂','九广铁路公司','2002 年 11 月 18 日 - 2004 年 07 月 30 日','<p>本项目内所有工程，都是在紧贴现有火车路轨旁或在其上进行。而罗湖站连接罗湖关口，为香港通往深圳最重要的通道。每日人流量超过十万人次，而在节日和主要假期，人流更高达每日三十万人次。其繁忙程度，可以想见。为确保铁路、车站以及关口的正常运作，以免影响正常使用的人士，承建商采取了相应的安全操施及安排，其中包括：大量的工程项目改在晚间，即火车服务停止后进行；提供大量而且稳固的栏栅及工台等用来隔开工程进行的范围和火车的服务范围；实施有效的安全工作程序包括路轨守望员等以确保列车及罗湖站的运作不受工程影响。</p><br/><br/>',31.00),(202,'kfsshp0g1rffwzc55tavx5yf','羅湖站改善工程：一號至三號月臺，連接橋及車站大堂 (九廣鐵路 東鐵合約編號：2002-0092)','2025-05-30 09:00:03.156000','2025-07-07 07:15:24.185000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','羅湖站改善工程：一號至三號月臺，連接橋及車站大堂','九廣鐵路公司','2002 年 11 月 18 日 - 2004 年 07 月 30 日','<p>本專案內所有工程，都是在緊貼現有火車路軌旁或以上進行。而羅湖站側連接羅湖關口，爲香港通往深圳最重要的通道。每日人流超過十萬人次，而在節日或主要假期，人流更高達三十萬人次。其繁忙情度，可以想見。爲確保鐵路，車站以至關口的運作正常，以免影響使用的人士，承建商採取了相應的安全操施及安排，其中包括了：大量的工程項目改在晚間，當火車服務停止後進行；提供大量而又穩固的欄柵及工台等以分格工程進行的範圍及火車的服務範圍；實施有效的安全工作程式包括路軌守望員等以確保列車及羅湖站的運作不受工程進行影響。</p>',31.00),(204,'yy0na0xmiy60dofys447ko9u','沙田污水處理廠第三期擴建第二部份工程 (合約編號：DC/2001/01)','2025-05-30 09:02:45.388000','2025-07-07 07:15:23.209000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','沙田污水處理廠第三期擴建第二部份工程','渠務署','2002 年 03 月 08 日 - 2005 年 10 月 18 日','<p>主要工程包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造六個初級沉澱缸及相關之初級污水泵房，占地五千零六十平方米</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造六個曝氣池及與其相關之兩個污水出/入口控制室，占地約七千六百九十米</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造一個深度約八米之排水泵房</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造十二個終級沉澱缸，共佔地七千一百五十米</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造一個平面面積約四百五十米的回流污泥泵房，二個砂礫分類裝置，二個引水溝渠及充氣砂礫溝渠</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造沙井，管道，溝渠，線坑、線井，浮渣井，雨水渠，氣喉及處理廠內的道路</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>四百支一米直徑，深度約三十至五十余米(至石層)之現澆攪拌樁及八百七十八支直徑二百一十九毫米，深度約二十五至四十米(至石層)之迷你樁</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>鋪設由二百毫米至一千六百毫米直徑之各類型管道，其中包括鋼管，熟鐵喉管及預製鋼筋混凝土喉管等，總長度約一千五百米</li></ul>',32.00),(206,'gvqhwzvi1fqn5hh3xw31d74y','沙田污水处理厂第三期扩建第二部份工程 (合约编号：DC/2001/01)','2025-05-30 09:03:09.665000','2025-07-07 07:15:20.686000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','沙田污水处理厂第三期扩建第二部份工程','渠务署','2002 年 03 月 08 日 - 2005 年 10 月 18 日','<p>工程內容主要包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造六个初级沉淀缸及相关之初级污水泵房，占地五千零六十平方米</li><li>建造六个曝气池及与其相关之两个污水出/入口控制室，占地约七千六百九十米</li><li>建造一个深度约八米之排水泵房</li><li>建造十二个终级沉淀缸，共占地七千一百五十米</li><li>建造一个平面面积约四百五十米的回流污泥泵房，二个砂砾分类装置，二个引水沟渠及充气砂砾沟渠</li><li>建造沙井，管道，沟渠，线坑、线井，浮渣井，雨水渠，气喉及处理厂内的道路</li><li>四百支一米直径，深度约三十至五十余米(至石层)之现浇搅拌桩及八百七十八支直径二百一十九毫米，深度约二十五至四十米(至石层)之迷你桩</li><li>铺设由二百毫米至一千六百毫米直径之各类型管道，其中包括钢管，熟铁喉管及预制钢筋混凝土喉管等，总长度约一千五百米</li></ul>',32.00),(208,'vkk01uzp1vqyaio66h8mslnd','Construction of Shatin Sewage Treatment Works Stage III Extenstion Phase II (Contract No. DC/2001/01)','2025-05-30 09:09:23.227000','2025-07-07 07:15:10.062000',NULL,8,36,'en','Construction of Shatin Sewage Treatment Works Stage III Extenstion Phase II','Sewerage Projects Division','08 March 2002 - 18 October 2005','<p>The major element of works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 6 primary sedimentation tanks and the associated primary sludge pumping station with a total footprint of 5060m2</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 6 aeration tanks and the 2 associated aeration tank control rooms with a total footprint of 7690m2.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 1 drainage pumping station with a depth of approximately 8m.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 12 final sedimentation tanks with a total footprint of 7150m2.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 1 RAS pumping station with a footprint of 450m2, 2 grit classifiers, 2 flume channels and 1 aerated grit channel</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the chambers, ducts, pipes, channels, trenches, drawpits , scum pits, drains, road, air main, and painting works</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of piled foundations including 400 nos. of 1m diameter bored piles and 878 nos. of 219mm diameter mini piles</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Supply and lay D.I. mild steel and precast concrete pipes with diameter ranging from 200mm to 1600mm, where the total length is approximately 1.5km</li></ul>',32.00),(210,'slef5hihq87y7kko51bw54ef','Noise Mitigation Measures at Hong Lok Yuen Section (Contract No. 1/ICP/2000)','2025-05-30 09:13:06.645000','2025-07-07 07:15:11.948000',NULL,8,36,'en','Noise Mitigation Measures at Hong Lok Yuen Section','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','01 November 2000 - 07 July 2001','<p>Since the work was carried out during train service hours, a chain link fence had to be erected to separate the live tracks and the work area. Moreover, during construction period, special care had to be taken particularly on erecting structural steel posts and acoustic panels ensuring no object would obstruct the tracks, and no object nor person would come within reach the 2.75m regime of the KCRC’s high voltage equipment in lifting operation.</p><br/><p>The limited access to the work area also made the concreting work difficult and risky as specially long tremie pipe of 400m had to be connected from Hong Lok Yuen Road to the southern end of the Site for casting footing and upstand.</p><br/><p>Part of the site&#x27;s loading / unloading area occupied the road area owned by Hong Lok Yuen(HLY), but since the site was closed to HLY, the project management team had to liaise with the HLY Management Office for permission of road use and settle any complaints raised during construction. Fortunately a harmonious relationship was maintained with the HLYMO and its residents and no complaints were received throughout the construction period.</p>',33.00),(212,'ha5r144udlrm4neq7gzc95d0','康乐园隔音措施 (九广铁路公司)','2025-05-30 09:13:40.134000','2025-07-07 07:15:22.808000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','康乐园隔音措施','合约编号：1/ICP/2000','2000 年 11 月 01 日 - 2001 年 07 月 07 日','<p>由于施工安排在列车工作时间进行，因此必须先放置铁丝网栏将施工现场的铁轨和工作区隔开。此外，施工期间，在竖立结构钢柱和安装隔音板时要额外注意，确保没有物体误落入铁轨；并且，在起重操作过程中，任何人、任何物体都不能触碰到2.75米高的高电压设备。</p><br/><p>由于对进出施工现场的限制，令混凝土输送出现困难，特别是用作基脚及竖立构件的混凝土要从康乐园路经过400米长水下浇注管送到工地南侧显得更加危险。</p><br/><p>工地与康乐园十分接近，部分装卸货区的道路属康乐园范围。工程需得到康乐园管理处对路面使用的批准及承诺处理施工过程中收到的任何投诉。最后，工程在没有收到任何投诉及与康乐园管理处友好合作关系下顺利完成。</p>',33.00),(214,'xbqh521v8lbgiv0z5m24ljmt','康樂園隔音措施 (合約編號：1/ICP/2000)','2025-05-30 09:14:21.218000','2025-07-07 07:15:23.945000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','康樂園隔音措施','九廣鐵路公司','2000 年 11 月 01 日 - 2001 年 07 月 07 日','<p>由於施工時間在列車服務期間進行，必須先設置一個欄分隔開現有的路軌和工作區。此外，豎立垂直的鋼柱及安裝隔音板須特別小心，以確保沒有任何物件誤落路軌，及沒有任何人能觸及在2.75米高的高電壓設備的起重操作。</p><p>由於工作區有進出限制，令運送混凝土出現困難，由康樂園路經過400米長水下澆注管把混凝土送住地盤南端作基腳及豎立構件之用極具挑戰。</p><p>地盤與康樂園十分接近，部分裝卸貨區的道路亦屬康樂園範圍。工程需得到康樂園管理處對路面使用的批准及承諾處理施工過程中的任何投訴。最後工程在沒有任何投訴及與康樂園管理處友好合作關係下順利完成。</p><br/><br/>',33.00),(216,'xpwx4xbx8jt9b620fzxo3gmi','九廣鐵路減音措施 – 九龍塘和大埔 (合約編號：1/ICP/1999)','2025-05-30 09:15:13.238000','2025-07-07 07:15:24.263000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','九廣鐵路減音措施 – 九龍塘和大埔','九廣鐵路','1999 年 10 月 01 日 - 2001 年 02 月 28 日','<p>在現有路軌上建造2.9公里隔音屏及逃生樓梯，包括建造小口徑樁、地基、相關的電力裝置及消防設備電力裝置</p>',34.00),(218,'imktawfe7yj9my621vrnawew','九广铁路九龙塘至大埔沿线减噪音项目 (合约编号：1/ICP/1999)','2025-05-30 09:15:51.162000','2025-07-07 07:15:23.132000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','九广铁路九龙塘至大埔沿线减噪音项目','九广铁路','1999 年 10 月 01 日 - 2001 年 02 月 28 日','<p>在原有路轨上建造2.9公里隔音屏及逃生楼梯，包括微型桩筏基础和相关电气安装和消防设备</p>',34.00),(220,'apimd96btjmpmvku7xylao1i','Noise Mitigation Measures at KowloonTong and Tai Po Section (Contract No. 1/ICP/1999)','2025-05-30 09:16:34.694000','2025-07-07 07:15:10.964000',NULL,8,36,'en','Noise Mitigation Measures at KowloonTong and Tai Po Section','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','01 October 1999 - 28 February 2001','<p>A construction of a 2.9km low rise noise barrier and escape footpath and stairs along the existing live railway track are to be constructed. The works include mini-pile and raft foundation and associated electrical installation and fire services. </p>',34.00),(222,'acuq6mom039j78vrmjo7j1sd','Nam Cheong Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-402)','2025-05-30 09:23:10.103000','2025-07-07 07:15:09.905000',NULL,8,36,'en','Nam Cheong Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','01 October 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Nam Cheong Station is the southern terminal of the West Rail. It is an interchange station for the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The structure envelopes the alignments of the existing elevated West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the existing Airport Express Line (AEL) and the MTR Tung Chung Line. It also includes the linking carriageway and the associated elevated flyover system. During the construction stage, the West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line have to maintain normal operations. These requirements greatly increased the difficulties in the construction and required extremely high and stringent construction techniques.</p><br/><p>This station includes the track side platforms at ground level and an underground station hall for both the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The underground station hall was constructed underneath the operating Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line. In order to ensure the operation of the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line, “Top down” construction method was employed. This kind of construction method on such a scale is seldom seen in Hong Kong.The underground station hall and platform design ensured the utilization and development of the underground space, and reduce occupied area at ground level. It also provided a grand outlook of the station. Apart from providing business activities, with the highly efficient pedestrian flow design, the crowds are quickly diverted to the relevant Airport Express Line station, bus station, residential blocks and commercial areas.</p><br/><p>The column, beam structure and foundation design of the station have made provisions for the future development of multi-storey residential blocks on top of the station. The foundations design includes large diameter cast in-situ concrete bored piles, diaphragm walls and driven steel H-piles, etc. Reinforced concrete column structures were reserved at the roof slab of the station for future construction of the multi-storey resident blocks. The multi-storey shear walls of the future superstructures will be supported by the transfer plate at the station roof. This accommodates any future change in the layout of the superstructure.</p>',35.00),(224,'ove1qrzkkyvl1pmuhj8wphyt','南昌站 (九广铁路 西铁合约编号CC-402)','2025-05-30 09:23:58.263000','2025-07-07 07:15:23.013000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','南昌站','九广铁路','1999 年 10 月 01 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>南昌站作为西铁第一期的南面总站，是西铁及地铁东涌线的共享综合车站。车站的构造，不仅覆盖了现有的西九龙高架高速公路及机场快线、地铁东涌线，同时，也包括了相关的连接行车道路与高架桥梁系统。另外，在车站建设施工期间，要保持西九龙高架高速公路、机场快线及东涌线正常运作的要求，为施工带来了不少难度。因此，对施工的技术要求是非常高和严格的。</p><br/><p>本车站设有地面沿车轨站台，以及与地铁东涌线共用的地底车站大堂。该大堂建于正在营运中的机场铁路及东涌线的地底。为确保机场铁路及东涌线正常运作，所以特别选择以「从上而下」（top-down）的建筑方式兴建，其规模在香港实属罕见。地底车站大堂及站台设计配合地下空间进行最大限度的开发及利用，减少占用地面的空间，也确保外观的宏伟。在提供商业活动的同时，也利于乘客流向的疏导，凭借高效人流引导设计迅速将乘客引导至最近的机场快线车站、公共汽车站、住宅及商业区。</p><br/><p>为配合将来在车站顶棚会建筑多幢多层式的住宅物业及高层商业大厦，车站的梁、柱结构及其基础的设计作出了相应的预备工作，其基础包括多种不同类型的椿基：如大口径现浇钢筋混凝土搅拌椿、地下连续墙及打入式工字型钢椿等等。车站施工期间，在车站顶部预留了大楼底层的钢筋混凝土柱结构。将来上盖物业发展时，站顶平台会以平板多肢结构承托上盖的多层剪力墙，这对将来顶棚以上的楼宇设计时产生的任何变动，是一个弹性的处理方法。</p>',35.00),(226,'hfht15rmopyjseas5xdclubd','南昌站 (九廣鐵路 西鐵合約編號CC-402)','2025-05-30 09:27:27.767000','2025-07-07 07:15:24.589000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','南昌站','九廣鐵路','1999 年 10 月 01 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>南昌站是西鐵第一期的南面總站，爲西鐵及地鐵東涌線之共用綜合車站。車站的結構，不但覆蓋了現有之西九龍高架高速公路及機場快線、地鐵東涌線，同時，也包括了相關的連接行車道路與高架橋樑系統。在車站建設施工期間，西九龍高架高速公路，機場快線及東涌線要保持如常運作，這些要求，爲施工帶來了不少難度。因此，對施工的技術要求亦十分高和嚴格。</p><br/><p>本車站設有地面沿車軌月臺及與地鐵東涌線共用的地底車站大堂。該大堂建於正在營運中之機場鐵路及東涌線的地底。爲確保機場鐵路及東涌線如常運作，所以特別選擇以「從上而下」（top-down）的建築方式興建，其規模爲香港僅見。地底車站大堂及月臺設計配合地下空間的儘量開發及善用，減少地面空間的佔用，亦確保地面外觀宏偉吸引，同時提供商業活動之餘，亦方便乘客流向的疏導，以高效率設計迅速將人流導至相鄰的機鐵車站、公共汽車站、住宅及商業區。</p><br/><p>爲配合未來在車站上蓋將會發展多幢多層式的住宅物業及高層商業大廈，車站的梁、柱結構及其基礎的設計作出了相應的預備工夫，其基礎包括多種不同類型的椿基：如大口徑現澆鋼筋混凝土攪拌椿、地下連續牆及打入式工字形鋼椿等等。車站施工期間，於車站頂部預留大樓底層之鋼筋混凝土柱結構。將來上蓋物業發展時，站頂平臺會以平板多肢結構承托上蓋的多層剪力牆，對未來上蓋樓宇設計時可産生的任何變動，是一個保留彈性的處理方法。</p>',35.00),(228,'r9w25perwwp3fdy99lpq7l55','薄扶林道及沙孫道交通交匯處 (合約編號：HY/98/10)','2025-05-30 09:29:15.206000','2025-07-07 07:15:23.756000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','薄扶林道及沙孫道交通交匯處','路政署','1998 年 12 月 16 日 - 2003 年 03 月 31 日','<p>本專案的重點爲擴闊一段在全港規模最大，最主要的瑪麗醫院前的薄扶林道與及改善其鄰近的路口，提供一個暢通無阻的交匯處。確保緊急車輛能夠儘快進出醫院，也改善附近一帶地區的交通流量。在擴闊薄扶林道的部份，工程包括在陡峭的斜坡上建造一段高架行車道。同時，也包括把現有的薄扶林道拉直及重建。並重建沙孫道及薄扶林道路口。此外，本專案也包括以重建的沙孫道爲起點，建造一條連接瑪麗醫院的連接橋。重建班士尼道與薄扶林道路口。其部份路面也是於斜坡上興建的高架行車道。由於大部份的高架行車道的結構工程都是在陡峭的斜坡上進行，工程的難度大大的提高。尤其是在進行基礎工程的階段。爲建造現澆攪拌樁承建商採用了大規模的臨時工作臺及在斜坡上開挖的臨時平臺。薄扶林道爲連接港島西區及南區的其中一條主要通道，交通流量非常高，車速又快。於工程進行期間，爲確保交通安全及暢順，承建商提供了大量的相關操施，包括：建造臨時擴闊路面，提供及安裝大量的交通標置，指示及照明系統等。</p>',36.00),(230,'pahx7rp9q7qnw0knv3o4jgem','薄扶林道及沙孙道交通交汇处 (合约编号：HY/98/10)','2025-05-30 09:29:58.625000','2025-07-07 07:15:22.974000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','薄扶林道及沙孙道交通交汇处','路政署','1998 年 12 月 16 日 - 2003 年 03 月 31 日','<p>本项目的重点为扩阔一段在全港规模最大，最主要的玛丽医院前的薄扶林道与及改善其邻近的路口，提供一个畅通无阻的交汇处。确保紧急车辆能够尽快进出医院，也改善附近一带地区的交通流量。在扩阔薄扶林道的部份，工程包括在陡峭的斜坡上建造一段高架行车道。同时，也包括把现有的薄扶林道拉直及重建。并重建沙孙道及薄扶林道路口。此外，本项目也包括以重建的沙孙道为起点，建造一条连接玛丽医院的连接桥。重建班士尼道与薄扶林道路口。其部份路面也是于斜坡上兴建的高架行车道。由于大部份的高架行车道的结构工程都是在陡峭的斜坡上进行，工程的难度大大的提高。尤其是在进行基础工程的阶段。为建造现浇搅拌桩承建商采用了大规模的临时工作台及在斜坡上开挖的临时平台。薄扶林道为连接港岛西区及南区的其中一条主要通道，交通流量非常高，车速又快。于工程进行期间，为确保交通安全及畅顺，承建商提供了大量的相关操施，包括：建造临时扩阔路面，提供及安装大量的交通标置，指示及照明系统等。</p>',36.00),(232,'gz7trmkru904m37rqvrudic3','Interchange at Pok Fu Lam Road and Sassoon Road (Contract No. HY/98/10)','2025-05-30 09:31:38.092000','2025-07-07 07:15:12.136000',NULL,8,36,'en','Interchange at Pok Fu Lam Road and Sassoon Road','Highways Department','16 December 1998 - 31 March 2003','<p>Widening of the section of Pok Fu Lam Road fronting Queen Mary Hospital involving the construction of new carriageway (partly on elevated structures) and reconstruction of existing carriageway; re-alignment of the upper section of Sassoon Road at its junction with Pok Fu Lam Road involving the replacement of the existing carriageway with new carriageway (partly on elevated structures); construction of a link bridge linking the re-aligned Sassoon Road and the access road to Queen Mary Hospital; re-alignment of the upper section of Bisney Road at its junction with Pok Fu Lam Road involving the replacement of existing carriageway with new carriageway (partly on elevated structures); demolition of the existing footbridge across Pok Fu Lam Road and construction of a new footbridge at the same location; and associated drainage, landscaping, retaining walls and slope works.</p>',36.00),(234,'ww6jq7kjvb5pcfixpi79e2vn','Noise Mitigation Measures at Peace Avenue and Ho Man Tin Street (KCRC Contract No. 2/ICP/1997)','2025-05-30 09:32:25.036000','2025-07-07 07:15:11.004000',NULL,8,36,'en','Noise Mitigation Measures at Peace Avenue and Ho Man Tin Street','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','01 August 1997 - 31 May 1999','<p>Significant restrictions included limited access to the site due to its close proximity to the operating railway and surrounding road network, as well as difficulty in accessing the site due to the topography with 60% of the site located on an elevated fill embankment with slopes up to 38°. The critical concern to ensure there would be no disruption to the railway&#x27;s normal operation presented the biggest challenge to this project.</p>',37.00),(236,'kmn9fontpuy0q4x50zln71ed','九广铁路减音措施 – 太平道和何文田街 (合约编号：2/ICP/1997)','2025-05-30 09:33:08.797000','2025-07-07 07:15:21.744000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','九广铁路减音措施 – 太平道和何文田街','九广铁路','1997 年 08 月 01 日 - 1999 年 05 月 31 日','<p>由于施工地点非常接近道路网和运营中的铁路且60%的施工现场位于斜坡达38°的高架路堤上，而业主着重要关注的是确保工程施工进行期间要不阻碍铁路正常运行，因此造就工程的最大难度的挑战。</p>',37.00),(238,'icfjn73o96050ehzj19vu67i','九廣鐵路減音措施 – 太平道和何文田街 (合約編號：2/ICP/1997)','2025-05-30 09:33:47.653000','2025-07-07 07:15:23.684000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','九廣鐵路減音措施 – 太平道和何文田街','九廣鐵路','1997 年 08 月 01 日 - 1999 年 05 月 31 日','<p>由於施工地點非常接近道路網及營運中的鐵路。以及60％的工地位於斜坡達 38 °的高架路堤上難以抵達。要確保工程進行期間沒有阻礙鐵路正常運作，這成為此工程的最大挑戰。</p>',37.00),(240,'viun41wyab9cyy1s8hvbq602','內河碼頭辦公室及貨倉大樓','2025-05-30 09:34:42.447000','2025-07-07 07:15:24.432000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','內河碼頭辦公室及貨倉大樓','屯門內河碼頭公司','1997 年 03 月 01 日 - 1998 年 08 月 01 日','<p>工程的主要內容包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造承扥大樓的樁柱及地基</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造大樓之樓房結構</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造貯油缸及液體燃料貯存設施</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>設計，供應及安裝卷閘</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>樓房機電工程</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>樓房裝修工程</li></ul>',38.00),(242,'yru0g2108imayswh2x4ojy0w','内河码头办公室及货仓大楼','2025-05-30 09:35:39.392000','2025-07-07 07:15:20.822000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','内河码头办公室及货仓大楼','屯门内河码头公司','1997 年 03 月 01 日 - 1998 年 08 月 01 日','<p>工程的主要内容包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造承扥大楼的桩柱及地基</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造大楼的楼房结构</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造贮油缸及液体燃料贮存设施</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>设计，供应及安装卷闸</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>楼房机电工程</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>楼房装修工程</li></ul>',38.00),(244,'x9fwcd1v1hh2w5argebvra7s','C&E Office, Queen\'s Warehouse and Agent\'s Offices','2025-05-30 09:36:36.493000','2025-07-07 07:15:09.906000',NULL,8,36,'en','C&E Office, Queen\'s Warehouse and Agent\'s Offices','River Trade Terminal Co. Ltd','01 March 1997 - 01 August 1998','<p>The major element of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of piles and foundation</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of building structures</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Fuel storage tanks enclosure and LPG storage facility construction</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Design, supply and installation of roller shutters</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>E&amp;M Works for the buildings</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Fit out works</li></ul>',38.00),(246,'zyr93ou28z4be1ecv496mqgw','Tung Chung Development Phase 1 – Infrastructure (Contract No. NL 2/93)','2025-05-30 09:40:31.843000','2025-07-07 07:15:20.259000',NULL,8,36,'en','Tung Chung Development Phase 1 – Infrastructure','Territory Development Department','01 July 1994 - 31 January 1997','<p>The bridge was supported by two land abutments and six marine piers. Each abutment was supported by twelve 1.5m diameter land bored piles up to 56m long and each marine pier was supported by twelve 1.5m diameter marine piles.</p><br/><p>The 1.5m diameter permanent linings of the marine bored piles were spliced into 24m to 30m lengths and pitched in position by piling barge.</p>',39.00),(248,'sa7nhye0bcyqbeijg82yykqd','东涌发展第一期基建工程 (合约编号：2/93)','2025-05-30 09:41:22.540000','2025-07-07 07:15:21.406000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','东涌发展第一期基建工程','拓展署','1994 年 07 月 01 日 - 1997 年 01 月 31 日','<p>此预应力混凝土桥支撑架构为六座海上桥墩及两端陆上桥座组成。每处桥座以十二支直径达一米半及长达五十六米之陆上螺旋桩为支撑，而每座海上桥墩以十二支直径达一米半之海上桩为支撑。</p><br/><p>海底基桩以驳船载运每节24-30米长之套管桩至定位钻掘接合而成。</p>',39.00),(250,'q8ff3su7ez55ooom60nwhof5','東涌發展第一期基建工程 (合約編號：2/93)','2025-05-30 09:41:56.342000','2025-07-07 07:15:24.648000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','東涌發展第一期基建工程','拓展署','1994 年 07 月 01 日 - 1997 年 01 月 31 日','<p>此預應力混凝土橋支撐架構爲六座海上橋墩及兩端陸上橋座組成。每處橋座以十二支直徑達一米半及長達五十六米之陸上螺旋樁爲支撐，而每座海上橋墩以十二支直徑達一米半之海上樁爲支撐。</p><br/><p>海底基樁以駁船載運每節24-30米長之套管樁至定位鑽掘接合而成。</p>',39.00),(252,'dk0gqvkl2z6q0b0dh8lfpwmz','沙田新市鎮城第II 階工程－T6 號道路及交匯處工程 (合約編號：ST45/87)','2025-05-30 09:43:28.910000','2025-07-07 07:15:25.494000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','沙田新市鎮城第II 階工程－T6 號道路及交匯處工程','拓展署','1988 年 06 月 01 日 - 1991 年 10 月 31 日','<p>此橋梁使用逾千噸之裝配式鋼管工作架。</p><br/><p>河中橋墩之樁帽採用預鑄模式施工法，在基樁施作不透水封及混凝土灌漿前，即將預鑄模以千斤頂固定於樁內。</p><br/><p>雙V型橋墩施工期間，須加打臨時樁以支撐工作架。</p><br/><p>現場灌築逾三百支大口徑螺旋樁。</p>',40.00),(254,'cgx4de3djdpyylgsubgpji69','沙田新市镇城第II 阶段工程－T6 号道路及交汇处工程 (合约编号：ST45/87)','2025-05-30 09:44:08.706000','2025-07-07 07:15:22.308000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','沙田新市镇城第II 阶段工程－T6 号道路及交汇处工程','拓展署','1988 年 06 月 01 日 - 1991 年 10 月 31 日','<p>此桥梁使用超过千吨之装配式钢管工作架。</p><br/><p>河中桥墩之桩帽采用预铸模式施工法，在基桩施作不透水封及混凝土灌浆前，即将预铸模以千斤顶固定于桩内。</p><br/><p>双V型桥墩施工期间，须加打临时桩以支撑工作架。</p><br/><p>现场灌筑逾三百支大口径螺旋桩。</p>',40.00),(256,'e9jtx4hebml31agc8xy3g7b4','Sha Tin New Town, Stage II Road T6 and Interchanges (Contract No. ST45/87)','2025-05-30 09:44:59.205000','2025-07-07 07:15:14.722000',NULL,8,36,'en','Sha Tin New Town, Stage II Road T6 and Interchanges','Territory Development Department','01 June 1988 - 31 October 1991','<p>Over a thousand tonnes of fabricated steel false work was required for the high level bridge.</p><br/><p>Pile Caps for the marine bridge piers were constructed in precast concrete permanent shells which were lowered into position on the bored piles using strand jacks before making watertight seals and concreting.</p><br/><br/><p>Temporary piles were installed to support the false work for the reinforced concrete V-shaped piers.</p><br/><p>Over 300 large diameter bored piles were constructed by the company.</p>',40.00),(324,'vp94yuev60ex89i7d6e06rzk','Package Contract No. C84-0032 AOS Revitalization - Supply, Installation, Testing and Commissioning of Demolition and Re-Construction of Decking Package Contract','2025-05-30 06:33:25.046000','2025-07-07 07:15:05.888000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.580000',8,36,'en','Package Contract No. C84-0032 AOS Revitalization - Supply, Installation, Testing and Commissioning of Demolition and Re-Construction of Decking Package Contract','New World Construction Company Limited','17 December 2015 - 16 September 2018','<p>The revitalization plan of Avenue of Stars (AOS) was announced in 2015 and the avenue was reopened in 2019.</p><p>The reconstruction of the deck structure along the avenue was one of the package contracts of the AOS revitalization project. The works include the demolition and reconstruction of the existing AOS deck structure, the reparation of existing crossheads and the installation of precast cladding panels. It also involves the demolition and reconstruction of the existing connecting bridge from AOS to Hotel InterContinental Hong Kong.</p><p>The AOS project was carried out under the spot lights of mass media. The major challenge facing by the project team is the short contract period. With an ambitious project timeframe, the demolition and reconstruction of around 400m long concrete bridge structure in marine condition is completed within 11 months. The project team is proud to successfully complete the project with high standard of project management in terms of public relation, quality assurance, programme monitoring, budget control, safety and environmental.</p>',3.00),(325,'gfgodjb43vdqfpomhldmxy3v','Management Contract for the Residential Development at No.420-422 Prince Edward Road West','2025-05-30 06:32:31.456000','2025-07-07 07:15:05.889000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.586000',8,36,'en','Management Contract for the Residential Development at No.420-422 Prince Edward Road West','Wise City Investment Limited','29 December 2015 - 14 May 2018','<p>The property is a residential development located at No.420-420 Prince Edward Road West, Kowloon City, Kowloon, Hong Kong. Build King enters into Management Contracts with the client and provides Management Services covering the construction of foundation and ELS works, the subsequent construction of superstructure, MEP, finishing and fitting-out package sub-contract works.</p><p>The major scope of work includes construction of a single 24-storey residential tower, including 4 levels of podium floors, 1 level for pump room and water tank, 17 level of residential floors and 2 levels for recreational facilities and club house. The building envelope of the tower is cladded with wall tiles and aluminum cladding. BIM is adopted in this project for MEP coordination of CSIDs and CBWDs. This project aims to achieve Bronze rating under the BEAM Plus for New Buildings.</p>',2.00),(326,'dpulb44qpxxfmn7pcdd8sxj1','Contract No. HY/2016/04 Elevated Walkway between Tong Ming Street and Tong Tak Street , Tseung Kwan O','2025-05-30 06:31:03.662000','2025-07-07 07:15:05.876000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.607000',8,36,'en','Contract No. HY/2016/04 Elevated Walkway between Tong Ming Street and Tong Tak Street , Tseung Kwan O','Highways Department','30 December 2016 - 03 March 2021','<p>The main purpose of this project is to construct an elevated walkway connecting the existing footbridge across Tong Ming Street to the shopping mall above Tseung Kwan O MTR Station and a lift at the end of the elevated walkway near Tong Tak Street to provide a comfortable and convenient access for residents (especially the elderly) of Tseung Kwan O town centre. The existing cycle parking area at Tong Ming Street is to be reconstructed and expanded to increase the number of cycle parking spaces for use by the residents of the area.</p><p>This contract mainly comprises construction of an elevated walkway of about 180 m in length and about 5 m in clear width, connecting the existing footbridge across Tong Ming Street to the shopping mall above Tseung Kwan O MTR Station; construction of a lift at the end of the proposed elevated walkway near Tong Tak Street; reconstruction and expansion of the existing cycle parking area; and ancillary works, including associated road, drainage, public utilities, public lighting, landscaping, and electrical and mechanical works.</p>',1.00),(327,'iys6zyx578zumj2ej5ijgyo3','Contract Ref: 8110030604 Foundation and Associated Works Contract for Main Works Package 1 for Expansion of United Christian Hospital (Sub-contract)','2025-05-30 06:34:59.863000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.475000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.737000',8,36,'en','Contract Ref: 8110030604 Foundation and Associated Works Contract for Main Works Package 1 for Expansion of United Christian Hospital (Sub-contract)','Hospital Authority','22 August 2015 - 20 August 2019','<p>The capacity in terms of space, service and existing facilities of United Hospital are inadequate to cope with the rising service demand for residents in Kowloon East, current service standards and future service needs. HA plans to improve and enhance the overall capacity of the hospital.</p><p>The major scope of this project consists of foundation construction for the future hospital expansion namely the new building “Block A”, “Block S Extension” and other associated works (incl. buildings demolition, A&amp;A works, diversion of drainage, sewers, freshwater &amp; salt watermain, gas, CLPP and telecom cables; construct new EVA and temperature transformer room, etc.)</p><p>The future Block A work comprises construction of large diameter bored piles, ELS construction and steel truss beam shoring. The new Block S foundation comprises rock socketed steel H piles and mini piles, and ELS utilizing pipe piles &amp; sheet piles. Road widening work will be required and foundation construction sequence will involve multiple staging due to its location &amp; site constraints.</p><p>Upon completion of the works, part of the services of the existing hospital building will be relocated to the new ambulatory block and the new extension block. The vacated area will be converted and refurbished to improve, expand and rationalize the various clinical and supporting services.</p>',4.00),(328,'z75kt072kz0p6kiaz0p0wvkw','Civil Engineering and Development Department Contract No. CV/2013/08 Liantang / Heung Yuen Wai Boundary Control Point Site Formation and Infrastructure Works – Contract 6','2025-05-30 06:35:49.259000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.540000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.810000',8,36,'en','Civil Engineering and Development Department Contract No. CV/2013/08 Liantang / Heung Yuen Wai Boundary Control Point Site Formation and Infrastructure Works – Contract 6','Civil Engineering and Development Department','24 June 2015 - 21 June 2019','<p>The LT/HYW BCP is the seventh land-based BCP between Hong Kong and Shenzhen. At present, there are two land-based BCPs at Man Kam To and Sha Tau Kok. Owing to geographical constraints, however, these two BCPs have little room for further expansion. Situated between Man Kam To and Sha Tau Kok, the LT/HYW BCP will make up for the inadequacies and make cross-boundary transportation and connections between Hong Kong and the eastern part of Guangdong Province as well as the Fujian and Jiangxi Provinces more convenient and efficient. This can help expand Hong Kong&#x27;s economic hinterland.</p><p>It comprises the construction of an approximately 4.6km long dual two-lane Connecting Road connecting the BCP with the proposed Sha Tau Kok Interchange and the associated tunnel ventilation buildings. Provision of sewage collection, treatment and disposal facilities for the BCP and the resite of Chuk Yuen Village and the associated environmental mitigation measures, and Environmental Monitoring and Audit (EM&amp;A)</p>',5.00),(329,'td3bzdqb8eyp23r1dmc3tee0','Shatin to Central Link Contract No. 1108 Kai Tak Station and Associated Tunnels','2025-05-30 07:08:45.522000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.540000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.802000',8,36,'en','Shatin to Central Link Contract No. 1108 Kai Tak Station and Associated Tunnels','MTR Corporation Limited','25 April 2013 - 18 November 2018','<p>The Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a government funded concessionary project providing a strategic rail corridor from Shatin to Central. One of the contracts of the Shatin to Central Link (SCL), the works comprise the construction of the Kai Tak Station and associate tunnels.</p><p>Consisting of 2 levels of RC box structure constructed by cut and cover method, this underground station is located in centre of Kai Tak Development Area. Upon completion of the project, Kai Tak residents will benefit as crossing the harbour will take much less time.</p>',8.00),(330,'oqyn5y6826z7m4zec9tf6q9c','Foundation and ELS Works for Proposed Logistic Centre at Tsing Yi Town Lot No. 180, N.T.','2025-05-30 07:21:24.741000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.560000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.829000',8,36,'en','Foundation and ELS Works for Proposed Logistic Centre at Tsing Yi Town Lot No. 180, N.T.','Goodear Development Limited','13 February 2012 - 08 May 2013','<p>Asia Logistics Hub is a logistic centre which is located in Tsing Yi with a gross floor area of 193,000 m2. It composes of a one-storey basement, a nine-storey warehouse and a six-storey office. In 2012, our group was awarded the foundation contract for the development. The works include constructing 107 nos. of large diameter bored piles and ELS and construction of pile caps and ground beams.</p>',12.00),(331,'dws0qnn3ekn5uc909u4l5i7e','Proposed Tseung Kwan O Joint Student Hostel The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology and The Hong Kong Baptist University','2025-05-30 07:10:09.268000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.519000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.837000',8,36,'en','Proposed Tseung Kwan O Joint Student Hostel The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology and The Hong Kong Baptist University','The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology','28 December 2012 - 02 June 2016','<p>To cater for the additional demand for student hostel places arising from the implementation of the four-year undergraduate curriculum and the further development of Hong Kong as a regional education hub, a number of University Grants Committee (UGC)-funded institutions are actively planning student hostel development projects, and the Tseung Kwan O Joint Student Hostel The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology and The Hong Kong Baptist University is one of these developments.</p><p>This 520-place student hostel is a 9 floor building with living accommodation facilities (bedrooms, dining rooms etc) and  common facilities (multi-purpose room &amp; kitchen, study room, gym room, laundry etc.) .  The Sky Garden at the 5th Floor offers a pleasant environment for leisure.</p>',9.00),(332,'hkqspqjxk8bppahqxikjuu8m','New World Centre Remodeling - Sea Deck A&A Work','2025-05-30 06:38:11.053000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.598000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.873000',8,36,'en','New World Centre Remodeling - Sea Deck A&A Work','New World Construction Company Limited','17 December 2013 - 17 March 2016','<p>The demolition and reconstruction works of New World Centre commenced in January 2009. In line with its business development plan, Sea Deck with an area of about 18 meters by 94 meters werel also reconstructed.</p><p>The project is divided into two phases: the first phase involved the demolition and alteration of existing sea deck (Area A to C), and the reconstruction of reinforced concrete sea deck (Area A to C). Apart from demolishing and reconstructing the remaining sea deck, the second phase also requires the construction of a bored pile of 800 mm in diameter inside the existing two-metre caissons. Crossing the two phases of the project also was the fabrication and installation of precast concrete intake channel about 30 metres long by 2.5 metres high and 5.6 to 10 metres wide.</p><p>Although the site was near the sea, subject to the &quot;Avenue of Stars&quot; in the south, marine works machinery could not be used because of the lack of access. Instead only onshore cranes and construction of temporary platforms when could be relied on considering the construction plan. Due to the Protection of the Harbour Ordinance, extension of the temporary platforms in existing structure and lifting method were used instead of seabed-based supporting methods.</p><p>As the site was very close to the hotel and tourist area, apart from increasing resources to reduce the noise, we also had to implement the demolition works within a limited time according to the hotel&#x27;s requirements so as to maintain the normal operation of the hotel. However, due to the limited available work space and the need to coordinate with other site works, resources could not be increased simply at any time to catch up with the progress. Therefore, project team had to find alternative ways to shorten the construction time at each stage of the construction.</p>',7.00),(333,'wagvwbany1pw5yr5sfawfmu5','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Design and Build Contract for Footbridge Linking Phase 8 Development','2025-05-30 06:37:14.614000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.596000','2025-07-07 07:15:06.921000',8,36,'en','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Design and Build Contract for Footbridge Linking Phase 8 Development','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University','15 June 2015 - 29 August 2019','<p>The major scope of this project comprises the design and construction of a footbridge linking the Main Campus and the Phase 8 development of The Hong Kong Polytechnic University. The footbridge is designed as a steel bow-string arch structure with a main span length of 68m across the entire Chatham Road South. The pedestrian walkway with an overall width of about 7m and its associated sub-structures are hung from the two main arch beams by high-tensioned steel bar. The aesthetic form of the footbridge is designed according to the concept of &quot;Flying Fish&quot; and echoes with the surrounding iconic buildings of the University.</p><p>The works under the project include the design and construction of pile foundation, pile cap, RC lift shaft structures, lift installation, steel footbridge structure and its associated sub- structures, architectural works and finishes, building services works, footbridge connection works involving alternation and addition works to the existing Block Z at Phase 8 development.</p>',6.00),(334,'i4ljh5vfixc3aga4c4gxs378','Admiralty Integrated Station and SCL Enabling Works (South Island Line (East) – Contract 901)','2025-05-30 07:22:18.694000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.022000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.535000',8,36,'en','Admiralty Integrated Station and SCL Enabling Works','MTR Corporation Limited','18 May 2011 - 31 December 2016','<p>The South Island Line (East) is a medium-capacity railway connecting the MTR network at Admiralty to the Southern District of Hong Kong, via new stations at Ocean Park, Wong Chuk Hang, Lei Tung and South Horizons - a distance of approximately 7 km.</p><p>The primary objective of Contract 901 is to construct a new Admiralty Integrated Station in an urban centre with a very limited site area.  Under this contract, the existing Admiralty Station will be significantly extended to provide interchange facilities between the existing Tsuen Wan Line, the new South Island Line (East) and the proposed Shatin to Central Link. In addition to the four new platforms to be constructed below and adjacent to the existing station, the works include an interchange concourse, relocation of existing passenger entrances and external landscaping.</p><p>The Works under MTR Contract 901 comprise an extension east of the existing ADM station. The ADM integrated station will accommodate an interchange concourse, circulation areas and station cavern for SIL and SCL (Shatin Central Link). The extension is located under Harcourt Garden and is bounded by the existing ADM station, two existing finger platform box structures (Island Line and Tsuen Wan Line) and the existing underground Admiralty car park. The proposed platforms for SIL(E) and SCL will be constructed below and adjacent to the existing ADM.</p>',13.00),(335,'hpxux3d9g8z3p2b4rrybm64j','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1111 Hung Hom North Approach Tunnels','2025-05-30 07:15:51.746000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.024000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.541000',8,36,'en','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1111 Hung Hom North Approach Tunnels','MTR Corporation Limited','17 December 2012 - 18 November 2018','<p>The Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a government funded concessionary project providing a strategic rail corridor from Shatin to Central. One of the contracts of the Shatin to Central Link (SCL). The scope of work is included Tunnels Works, Foundation Works, Site Formation Works, Bridge Works, Noise Enclosure Works and Demolition Works. This is a challenging project in terms of geographical location and work complexity, as this construction site will passes through the aged urban town Hung Hom where a huge amount of utilities are underground. Due to the location, extensive TTM arrangements and utilities diversion and/or protection has to be undertaken.</p>',10.00),(336,'sechk2e7trtysil9d7owz2um','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No.1106 Diamond Hill Station','2025-05-30 07:17:24.935000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.263000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.693000',8,36,'en','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No.1106 Diamond Hill Station','MTR Corporation Limited','17 December 2012 - 18 November 2018','<p>The 17-kilometre SCL was a territory-wide strategic railway project involving 10 stations, amongst which Diamond Hill was one of the six interchange stations. Upon the completion of Diamond Hill Station, it will become a new interchange station for the future SCL and the existing Kwun Tong Line.</p><p>The scope of SCL1106 included construction of a new SCL concourse and platforms and a wide array of enhanced facilities including the installation of 3 new lifts, 12 escalators, additional ticket issuing machines, automatic teller machines, shops, and new public toilet facilities. The scope also include the relocation of heritage structures and archaeological diggings.</p>',11.00),(337,'d9rixf64uvkn7kwhwtoah5k9','Tseung Kwan O Further Development – Design and Build of Infrastructure Works for Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill Site (Phase I) (Contract No. HY/2009/05)','2025-05-30 07:31:21.213000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.524000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.725000',8,36,'en','Tseung Kwan O Further Development – Design and Build of Infrastructure Works for Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill Site (Phase I)','Highways Department','29 December 2009 - 03 April 2012','<p>The Tseung Kwan O Further Development is to improve the overall design of the town with the vision to build Tseung Kwan O into a new town that can boast of its convenience, unique urban design of quality living environment.</p><p>This is one of the Tseung Kwan O Further Development projects, which mainly improves the linkage between Tseung Kwan O Stage 1 landfill site and the adjacent areas for supporting the future recreational developments at the landfill site. It includes the construction of a 2.0km footpath and 1.6km cycle track connecting Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill site and Tseung Kwan O Town Centre South; construction of an approximate 140m long bridge for pedestrians and cyclists; construction of about 1 km of grasscrete paved access and landscape works.</p>',15.00),(338,'tchh4m3umbxvj4q6eoxvjri7','Proposed Extension to Hangar Two (also known as “Hangar Three”)','2025-05-30 07:29:45.083000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.483000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.777000',8,36,'en','Proposed Extension to Hangar Two (also known as “Hangar Three”)','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd.','14 May 2011 - 31 May 2012','<p>The project is the extension of the existing Hangar Two operated by Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd, namely as Hangar Three. The new third hangar aimed to complement the existing hangars in providing sufficient hangar spaces to meet the growing demand for aircraft hangars in Hong Kong.</p><p>Major works under the contract include the construction of an air-craft hangar building (approx. 80 m x 50m) with steel structure and metal cladding complete with hangar door, installation of the steel structure of the hangar building and providing all necessary protective painting at the fabrication yard and the construction of a group of one storey ancillary workshops, apron works, external paved roads, site works, plumbing, drainage installations and mechanical, ventilation and air conditioning and electrical installations.</p>',14.00),(339,'hz2q7vzgjt4dweselw1ggqch','Contract No. KL/2008/09 Kai Tak Development – Stage 1 Infrastructure Works at North Apron of Kai Tak Airport for Public Housing and Government Office Development','2025-05-30 07:37:22.534000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.532000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.767000',8,36,'en','Contract No. KL/2008/09 Kai Tak Development – Stage 1 Infrastructure Works at North Apron of Kai Tak Airport for Public Housing and Government Office Development','Civil Engineering and Development Department','15 July 2009 - 23 August 2013','<p>The major scope of this project comprises the construction of approximately 2.6m long roads within the Project Site including the control, management, maintenance and diversion of existing roads, 2 footbridge FB1 and FB4, associated drainage including box culverts, sewerage and watermain works, enhancement and extension works of existing subways SW1, enhancement works of existing subways SW3 and SW5, landscape hardworks and softworks and environmental mitigation measures.</p><p>The works include realignment of Concorde Road, and construction of local Roads L2, L3, L4 (part) and L15. In conjunction with these roadworks are the associated street furniture, road markings and tra¬c signs, works for the highways structures (Footbridges, Subway, Enhancement Works) across Prince Edward Road East, construction of drainage, sewerage and fresh and salt water supplies systems to serve the Public Rental Housing (PRH) sites and the KTGO.</p><p>The works also include construction of two box culverts BC1 &amp; BC2, a 2.5m x 2.5m box culvert at Road L3 and its connection to the existing Nullah No. 2 and 3.0m x 2.8m box culvert along the amenity strip of Road L2 and its connection to the existing Kai Tak Nullah respectively, demolition of an existing ramp at the EMSD Headquarters ramp at the EMSD Headquarters crossing the Cargo Circuit, abandon the existing Nullah No. 1 and pipes, construction of 5 footpath connections from Road L2 to Subway SW5 and Wang Kong Road, improvement works at Kai Shing Street / Kai Wah Street junction, construction and installation of electrical and mechanical works for the infrastructure serving the early development at the North Apron area including the PRH sites and KTGO, landscape softworks and landscape hardworks.</p>',16.00),(340,'vfaj0ngaua6rk5blvd5mq7eo','Noise Mitigation Measures at Wo Liu Hang, Fo Tan (Contract No. 2007-0003)','2025-05-30 07:39:55.489000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.582000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.802000',8,36,'en','Noise Mitigation Measures at Wo Liu Hang, Fo Tan','MTR Comporation Limited','17 March 2008 - 31 March 2010','<p>The major element of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Design, supply &amp; installation of aluminium acoustic panels.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of mini pile foundations, pile caps and retaining walls.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction and/or modification of escape walkways, stairs and exit doors.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Electrical, Mechanical and Fire Services installations at Wo Liu Hang St. &amp; Lok Lo Ha.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Architectural Builder’s Works and Finishes</li></ul>',17.00),(341,'fki1x1nzp64ndjz236ienfgs','Retrofitting of Noise Barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridge at Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches (Contract No. HY/2007/08)','2025-05-30 08:05:53.706000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.640000','2025-07-07 07:15:07.888000',8,36,'en','Retrofitting of Noise Barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridge at Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches','Highways Department','08 January 2008 - 09 July 2011','<p>The major elements of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of noise barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridgeat Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Associated structural modification works to existing bridge parapet and utility troughs</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Associated civil, geotechnical traffic aids, road pavement, drainage etc.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Utilities diversion</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works</li></ul>',18.00),(342,'ynl953hfddvhemlkzzm5gael','Site Formation and Foundation Contract for Community Colleg